Bono and the rest of U2 have pulled out of a TV appearance after the frontman fell off his bike in Central Park on Sunday.

The band canceled their weeklong 'residency' on NBC's Tonight Show with Jimmy Fallon after the 'spill', in which Bono, 54, hurt his arm.

In a statement on their website, Bono's bandmates - Adam Clayton, Larry Mullen and The Edge - wrote that the rocker hurt his arm when he took a tumble in the middle of New York City, and will need minor surgery.

