They wrote: 'It looks like we will have to do our Tonight Show residency another time - we're one man down.

'Bono has injured his arm in a cycling spill in Central Park and requires some surgery to repair it. 

'We're sure he'll make a full recovery soon, so we'll be back! Much thanks to Jimmy Fallon and everyone at the show for their understanding.'

It tops off an unfortunate week for the Irish singer, who was also inches from disaster in an air accident.

